    <statement><p>If a ball is throw straight up with a speed of <m>56\ {\textstyle\frac{\rm\mathstrut ft}{\rm\mathstrut s}}</m>, its height at time <m>t</m> (in seconds) is given by</p>
<p><me>h(t)=-8t^{2}+56t+2</me></p>
<p>Find the maximum height the ball reaches.</p>
<p><fillin characters="20" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>100\ {\rm ft}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
